		<Aux:document_text xml:lang="en-US">Changing the terms of payment for work so that they are worse for the worker is prohibited (article 102 of the Labour Code). At the same time, there are cases of wage arrears. For example, the total arrears for wages as of 1 February 2003 for all sectors of the economy was 29.1 million somoni. The State guarantees every worker the right to fair compensation for labor and to timely receipt of that compensation; free assistance in finding suitable work and jobs; working conditions that meet safety and health requirements; rest that is provided through the establishment of working hours, in the form weekly days off, a paid annual vacation and a shortened work day for a number of professions and jobs; reimbursement for work-related injury caused to health or property; unemployment protection; strike, etc. (article 4 of the Labour Code).</Aux:document_text>
